#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/server-hoist-static-io.md
M|rules|title: Hoist Static I/O to Module Level
M|rules|impact: HIGH
M|rules|impactDescription: avoids repeated file/network I/O per request
M|rules|tags: server, io, performance, next.js, route-handlers, og-image
M|rules|**Impact: HIGH (avoids repeated file/network I/O per request)**
M|rules|When loading static assets (fonts, logos, images, config files) in route handlers or server functions, hoist the I/O operation to module level. Module-level code runs once when the module is first imp
M|rules|**Incorrect (reads font file on every request):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|// app/api/og/route.tsx
M|rules|import { ImageResponse } from 'next/og'
M|rules|export async function GET(request: Request) {
M|rules|// Runs on EVERY request - expensive!
M|rules|const fontData = await fetch(
M|rules|new URL('./fonts/Inter.ttf', import.meta.url)
M|rules|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|rules|const logoData = await fetch(
M|rules|new URL('./images/logo.png', import.meta.url)
M|rules|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|rules|return new ImageResponse(
M|rules|<div style={{ fontFamily: 'Inter' }}>
M|rules|<img src={logoData} />
M|rules|Hello World
M|rules|</div>,
M|rules|{ fonts: [{ name: 'Inter', data: fontData }] }
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (loads once at module initialization):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|// app/api/og/route.tsx
M|rules|import { ImageResponse } from 'next/og'
M|rules|// Module-level: runs ONCE when module is first imported
M|rules|const fontData = fetch(
M|rules|new URL('./fonts/Inter.ttf', import.meta.url)
M|rules|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|rules|const logoData = fetch(
M|rules|new URL('./images/logo.png', import.meta.url)
M|rules|).then(res => res.arrayBuffer())
M|rules|export async function GET(request: Request) {
M|rules|// Await the already-started promises
M|rules|const [font, logo] = await Promise.all([fontData, logoData])
M|rules|return new ImageResponse(
M|rules|<div style={{ fontFamily: 'Inter' }}>
M|rules|<img src={logo} />
M|rules|Hello World
M|rules|</div>,
M|rules|{ fonts: [{ name: 'Inter', data: font }] }
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (synchronous fs at module level):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|// app/api/og/route.tsx
M|rules|import { ImageResponse } from 'next/og'
M|rules|import { readFileSync } from 'fs'
M|rules|import { join } from 'path'
M|rules|// Synchronous read at module level - blocks only during module init
M|rules|const fontData = readFileSync(
M|rules|join(process.cwd(), 'public/fonts/Inter.ttf')
M|rules|)
M|rules|const logoData = readFileSync(
M|rules|join(process.cwd(), 'public/images/logo.png')
M|rules|)
M|rules|export async function GET(request: Request) {
M|rules|return new ImageResponse(
M|rules|<div style={{ fontFamily: 'Inter' }}>
M|rules|<img src={logoData} />
M|rules|Hello World
M|rules|</div>,
M|rules|{ fonts: [{ name: 'Inter', data: fontData }] }
M|rules|)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Incorrect (reads config on every call):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|import fs from 'node:fs/promises'
M|rules|export async function processRequest(data: Data) {
M|rules|const config = JSON.parse(
M|rules|await fs.readFile('./config.json', 'utf-8')
M|rules|)
M|rules|const template = await fs.readFile('./template.html', 'utf-8')
M|rules|return render(template, data, config)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (hoists config and template to module level):**
M|rules|```typescript
M|rules|import fs from 'node:fs/promises'
M|rules|const configPromise = fs
M|rules|.readFile('./config.json', 'utf-8')
M|rules|.then(JSON.parse)
M|rules|const templatePromise = fs.readFile('./template.html', 'utf-8')
M|rules|export async function processRequest(data: Data) {
M|rules|const [config, template] = await Promise.all([
M|rules|configPromise,
M|rules|templatePromise,
M|rules|])
M|rules|return render(template, data, config)
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|When to use this pattern:
M|rules|- Loading fonts for OG image generation
M|rules|- Loading static logos, icons, or watermarks
M|rules|- Reading cfg files that don't change at runtime
M|rules|- Loading email templates or other static templates
M|rules|- Any static asset that's the same across all requests
M|rules|When not to use this pattern:
M|rules|- Assets that vary per request or user
M|rules|- Files that may change during runtime (use caching with TTL instead)
M|rules|- Large files that would consume too much mem if kept loaded
M|rules|- Sensitive data that shouldn't persist in mem
M|rules|With Vercel's [Fluid Compute](https://vercel.com/docs/fluid-compute), module-level caching is especially effective because multiple concurrent requests share the same function instance. The static ass
M|rules|In traditional serverless, each cold start re-executes module-level code, but subsequent warm invocations reuse the loaded assets until the instance is recycled.